article.headline: Brase leads Princeton past Columbia 74-62

images.name: 1H CLMB M. Lo made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by L. Petrasek.
images.caption: 1H (17:24) CLMB Maodo Lo made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Luke Petrasek.

article.story: NEW YORK -- Hans Brase scored 15 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead four Princeton players in double figures as the Tigers beat Columbia 74-62 on Friday night. Ben Hazel finished with 13 -- all in the final 7:45 -- Amir Bell added 11 and Spencer Weisz 10 for Princeton (10-10, 3-1 Ivy League), which made 26 of 48 (54 percent) field goals, including 9 of 15 from 3-point range. Maodo Lo scored seven-straight Columbia points, including a three-point play that pulled the Lions within two about six minutes into the second half. Princeton used a 15-4 run, which was capped by a 3 from Hazel, to push its lead to 59-46 with 7:45 left. Lo, who finished with 21 points, scored 10-straight Columbia (10-9, 2-3) points -- including back-to-back 3s -- but the Lions would get no closer than down 10 the rest of the way.
